
TY  - JOUR
T1  - From Blue Sky Research to Problem Solving: A Philosophy of Science Theory of New Knowledge Production
AU  - Kilduff, Martin
AU  - Mehra, Ajay
AU  - Dunn, Mary B.
Y1  - 2011/04/01
PY  - 2011
DA  - 2011/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2009.0164
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2009.0164
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 297
EP  - 317
VL  - 36
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We examine rationalized logics developed within discourses of the philosophy of science for implications for the organization of new knowledge. These logics, derived from a range of philosophies (structural realism, instrumentalism, problem solving, foundationalism, critical realism) offer alternative vocabularies of motive, frameworks for reasoning, and guidelines for practice. We discuss the kinds of knowledge produced, the indicators of progress, the characteristic methods, exemplar organizations, and ways in which logics are combined and diffused.
AB  - We examine rationalized logics developed within discourses of the philosophy of science for implications for the organization of new knowledge. These logics, derived from a range of philosophies (structural realism, instrumentalism, problem solving, foundationalism, critical realism) offer alternative vocabularies of motive, frameworks for reasoning, and guidelines for practice. We discuss the kinds of knowledge produced, the indicators of progress, the characteristic methods, exemplar organizations, and ways in which logics are combined and diffused.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2009.0164
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.2009.0164
Y2  - 2026/04/24
