TY  - JOUR
T1  - How Contrastive Explanation Facilitates Theory Building
AU  - Tsang, Eric W. K.
AU  - Ellsaesser, Florian
Y1  - 2011/04/01
PY  - 2011
DA  - 2011/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2009.0153
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2009.0153
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 404
EP  - 419
VL  - 36
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We introduce the theory of contrastive explanation, the core argument of which is that we do not explain an entire phenomenon but only aspects of it. Using the example of transaction cost economics, we illustrate how contrastive explanation can assist organizational researchers in creating, broadening, and deepening their theories through posing suitable contrastive questions. We summarize our discussion into eight heuristic rules that will serve as useful theory-building tools.
AB  - We introduce the theory of contrastive explanation, the core argument of which is that we do not explain an entire phenomenon but only aspects of it. Using the example of transaction cost economics, we illustrate how contrastive explanation can assist organizational researchers in creating, broadening, and deepening their theories through posing suitable contrastive questions. We summarize our discussion into eight heuristic rules that will serve as useful theory-building tools.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2009.0153
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.2009.0153
Y2  - 2026/04/24
