T1  - Introduction to Special Topic Forum: Where are the New Theories of Organization?
AU  - Suddaby, Roy
AU  - Hardy, Cynthia
AU  - Huy, Quy Nguyen
Y1  - 2011/04/01
PY  - 2011
DA  - 2011/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.36.2.zok236
DO  - 10.5465/amr.36.2.zok236
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 236
EP  - 246
VL  - 36
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We summarize the manifest and latent content of the articles that make up the Special Topic Forum on Theory Development. Rather than offering new theories, however, most of the articles offer a series of critical accounts of current organizational theory and a range of novel ideas about the process of theory construction. We conclude by speculating about the institutional barriers to new theory creation and how those barriers might be changed.
AB  - We summarize the manifest and latent content of the articles that make up the Special Topic Forum on Theory Development. Rather than offering new theories, however, most of the articles offer a series of critical accounts of current organizational theory and a range of novel ideas about the process of theory construction. We conclude by speculating about the institutional barriers to new theory creation and how those barriers might be changed.
